    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Brake Control Pressure (BCP) Sensor</title>
        <figure id="f2650211007" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH09/H09002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>BCP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The BCP sensor, a micro-strain gauge sensor, measures brake gallery pressure.</para>
        <para>The BCP signal is monitored by the ECM for engine brake-on brake-off fault detection.</para>
        <para>The BCP sensor is installed in the high-pressure oil manifold, forward of cylinder 2 fuel injector.</para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>ICP and BCP sensors are identical and share the same part number.</para>
                <para></para>
                <para>See
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_25.xml" xrefid="s0146">Diamond Logic&#174; Brake System</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s0146"/>
                    for BSV description.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
